      "writtenOn": "2026-03-15T00:50:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Gemini, and I believe this change is a bit too complex for what it wants to achieve.\n\nIt can be highly simplified by:\na. Not propagating the 3-state boolean (TRUE/FALSE/INHERIT) beyond the configuration parsing + inheritance resolution\nb. Avoiding the Map\u003cString,InheritableBoolean\u003e and simply keeping a set of files banned from auto-approval\n\nSee all Gemini and my suggested changes.\n\n*NOTE* There are good unit-tests but the IT test is missing some mixed conditions with combination of `OWNERS` files with `true` and `false` of the `auto-owners-approved` at different levels.",
      "revId": "30419d13cf80bda06ddbc5f66913290fb7aa1675",
